    "description": "Burger King India is actively seeking a talented and motivated Department Manager to join our dynamic team in Chennai. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Burger King India:\nBurger King India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement promotional activities and in-store campaigns\n• Ensure compliance with company policies and retail regulations\n• Monitor inventory levels and coordinate replenishment activities\n• Maintain high standards of store hygiene and cleanliness\n• Assist in recruiting, onboarding, and performance management of staff\n• Manage store operations to ensure smooth daily functioning\n• Manage shrinkage and reduce stock discrepancies\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SAP Retail\n• Proficiency in CRM\n• Proficiency in E-commerce Integration\n• Proficiency in Planogram\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n• Proficiency in Omnichannel Retail\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Referral bonus program\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Burger King India!",
